description.plain:
Montero Lamar Hill (born April 9, 1999), better known by his stage name Lil Nas X, is a hip-hop artist, producer, and songwriter from Atlanta, Georgia. In 2018, he dropped out of college during his freshman year to pursue music full-time. Regarding this, he said:

Everybody thought I was crazy, I knew what I was doing. Thank you everyone, this just the mf beginning!

His stage name was originally meant to be a joke. In a January 2021 Jimmy Fallon interview, Nas revealed part of the origin of his stage name:

Nas was like my internet alias and then when I started doing music, I was like, “I want to have fun with this,” and every new rapper’s named Lil, Lil, Lil. What if I was Lil Nas? That’d be funny. So I was like, “Alright, bet. I’ll be Lil Nas.” And I added the X later on.

He then shared why he chose “Nas” as is internet alias during a Mike Tyson Interview on November 18th, 2022 where he stated:

When I was like a teenager, I had this guy who I was kinda like dating, but not really and his name was Nasir. Around that time, I started a Twitter account and I was like “You know what? I need a name but I don’t want people to know its me.” So, I was like “oh, lets just use Nas,” and I kinda got like stuck with it.

He then started to do music and realised lots of rappers have “Lil” in their name so he decided to be “Lil Nas”. He then says:

Then, it gets worse. It’s like “Okay, I’m Lil Nas now, blah blah blah post my music,” wait a minute, there’s another Lil Nas that exists on YouTube and Soundcloud. So I was like “I’m just gonna add an X”

Lil Nas X’s debut mixtape came in the form of NASARATI, released in July 2018. The mixtape was released on Youtube and Soundcloud, but after a lawsuit over its title track, “CARRY ON,” it was taken off the platforms. Following the mixtape’s release, Nas' breakthrough would come in the form of the December 2018 smash hit, “Old Town Road,” which blew up through TikTok memes and its April 2019 remix featuring country singer Billy Ray Cyrus.

The song entered the Billboard Hot 100 in March 2019, over a year after its original release. “Old Town Road” reached #1 on Spotify, iTunes and Apple Music, as well as becoming the first song to simultaneously chart on the Billboard country and hip-hop/R&B charts before it was disqualified from the country charts. The move by Billboard received a lot of backlash.

June 21, 2019 marked the release of his debut EP, 7. The EP received acclaim, including a GRAMMY nomination for “Album of the Year.” It debuted at #2 on the Billboard 200 selling 77,000 copies.

“Old Town Road (Remix)” became the most certified song ever in January 2021, with a 14x Platinum certification, representing 14 million equivalent song units sold. The same month, Lil Nas X released a children’s picture book, “C is For Country,” which became a New York Times Bestseller.

Lil Nas X released “MONTERO (Call Me By Your Name)” in March 2021, following it with the announcement of his first studio album, MONTERO, which was released on September 17 of the same year. The song took the world by the storm, with the music video receiving mixed receptions.

The Atlanta native would follow up the single with  May 2021 “SUN GOES DOWN” and July 2021’s collaboration with Jack Harlow, “INDUSTRY BABY.”

description.plain:
On “MONTERO (Call Me By Your Name),” Lil Nas X wants to stop pretending with his significant other and act on a first-name basis. The song’s title references Lil Nas X’s real name, Montero Lamar Hill.

The track first surfaced as a snippet on Twitter in July 9th, 2020. In November of the same year, Nas X stated that “Call Me By Your Name” would be the next song he’d release, announced via Instagram Live.

On February 2nd, 2021, a Super Bowl ad for Logitech starring Nas X was released, using the song. It was revealed in the ad’s description that the song was called “Montero (Call Me By Your Name).”

Lil Nas X later partnered with MSCHF, a company that makes viral products, to make a special edition of Nike Air Max 97s, known as the “Satan Shoes.” The shoes sold out in under a minute and the final pair, #666, was given out via a Twitter lottery. They were priced at $1,018, a reference to the Bible passage Luke 10:18, which reads: “I saw Satan fall like lightning from heaven.”



The release of the shoes, as well as the music video for the track, which sees Nas sliding down a pole into Hell and grinding on the Devil, garnered controversy among religious and conservative groups. However, the backlash only helped the song’s popularity.

description.plain:
On “Old Town Road,” Lil Nas X romanticizes the life of a cowboy. The character is unfulfilled by a hedonistic life of consumerism, substance abuse, and adultery. He also has dissatisfaction with the indolence of his peers, feeling no need to heed their advice. With nothing left to believe in or follow, the rider heads out with the only destination being the open road.

“Old Town Road” grew in popularity through numerous TikTok memes. Similarly to how the Atlanta duo iLOVEFRiDAY’s hit song “Mia Khalifa” blew up, clips on TikTok with the hashtag #oldtownroad have garnered millions of views.

After the song was removed from Billboard’s Country charts for “not (embracing) enough elements of today’s country music to chart in its current version,” Lil Nas X released a remix of his song with Billy Ray Cyrus to spite the company. The original eventually reached the number 1 spot on the Billboard Hot 100 on April 8, 2019.

Both the original version and the remix credits Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross of Nine Inch Nails for sampling their track, “34 Ghosts IV.”

description.plain:
“Panini” is the second single from Lil Nas X’s debut EP, 7, following his hit song, “Old Town Road”. It was first previewed on his Instagram on April 2, 2019, with the caption, “Sayyyyyy tooo meee.”

In this song, Lil Nas talks about his old fanbase and compares them to Panini, a character from the popular TV series Chowder.

Nas explained what he meant by the song in a Genius suggestion:

Panini was possessive over Chowder in the show. She’s a representation of fans of who love you when you’re small. Once you get the spotlight they aren’t feeling you as much. The song is not a diss but anger towards that fan but also wanting them back.

On May 12, 2019, Lil Nas premiered the song in its entirety for the first time at the Rolling Loud music festival.

songs.full_title: THATS WHAT I WANT by Lil Nas X
songs.title: THATS WHAT I WANT

description.plain:
On “THATS WHAT I WANT,” Lil Nas sings about his desire for love, which is often a struggle to find as a gay black man.

Lil Nas X first teased the song on TikTok in February 2021. The song was further teased in several TikToks starting May 28, 2021. A portion of the track played during the end credits of the “INDUSTRY BABY WITHOUT MUSIC” video, released on August 11. In collaboration with Taco Bell, the song was teased in their breakfast commercial, in which Lil Nas X made an appearance. Following the airing of the commercials, it was previewed on August 25, 2021, in the announcement video of the release date of MONTERO. The next day, the track was also previewed on the tracklist reveal.

Along with the album, the song was leaked in its entirety on August 6, 2021, more than one month before the release date.

songs.title: C7osure (You Like)

description.plain:
“C7osure (You Like)” finds Nas telling someone he loves (maybe, his fans or his family) that he needs to grow, and that fear or worry won’t hold him back: a similar theme is present on “Panini,” a more direct “letter” to those who have been disappointed by his rapid rise to fame.

The song was first teased on June 7, 2019, just two weeks before the release of the artist’s debut project.

On June 30, 2019, the last day of Pride Month, Hill went to Twitter in order to reveal the true personal meaning of the song, as he came out to the world by being his most authentic self in terms of his sexuality (as he seemingly declared himself to be a member of the LGBTQ+ community) and his music.

songs.full_title: SUN GOES DOWN by Lil Nas X
songs.title: SUN GOES DOWN

description.plain:
“SUN GOES DOWN” is the second single for Lil Nas X’s debut album MONTERO. Unlike the album’s anticipated prior single, “MONTERO,” this track’s existence was revealed by Nas X just a week prior to its release.

On the song, Lil Nas X portrays a younger self conflicted by his complexion and homosexuality, and dealing with loneliness. The artist explained in a tweet:

i named the song “sun goes down” because i feel like at night is when those thoughts you try to avoid really start to hit and you can’t escape them

While the chorus recalls past suicidal thoughts, the rest of the song carries a strong message of hope, as the sole verse ends with Nas X finding the outlet thanks to his 2019 coming-out.

The music video further reflects the introspective nature of the track and features a younger Lil Nas X struggling to find his place.

songs.title: STAR WALKIN’

description.plain:
“STAR WALKIN'” is a single by Lil Nas X, which he teased several times through Twitter and TikTok as early as May 2022. The song is the anthem of the League of Legends 2022 World Championship. The first time fans heard the full song was as an encore on the Long Live Montero tour in support of his MONTERO album, which started on September 6th, 2022.

On September 15th, 2022, Lil Nas announced a partnership with the multiplayer video game League of Legends to promote both “STAR WALKIN'” and the game’s 2022 World Championship. The company behind League of Legends, Riot Games, released a video wherein LNX acts as “Lil Nas Xecutive” and becomes the president of the company, playing “STAR WALKIN'” throughout their offices.

Initially slated to be released on September 23rd, the single’s release date moved up one day for unconfirmed reasons.

This song details lyrics about dysfunctional family relationships, depressive moments in life, and the hopelessness that one can feel in darker times. Introspective and honest, it adds another layer of depth and vulnerability to an already personal debut.

The track’s name was revealed on September 1st, 2021 in a tweet revealing the tracklist, and the music video shows images of a half-wild family home and LNX alone within it all.

songs.full_title: LOST IN THE CITADEL by Lil Nas X
songs.title: LOST IN THE CITADEL

description.plain:
“LOST IN THE CITADEL” storytells through a one-sided and ended relationship, where Lil Nas X’s “guardian angel” rejects his love and emotionally inflicts pain to him. Lil Nas X is now trying to recoup himself together and begin something new in his life.

Sonically, the song revolves around an electronic-pop track mixing with a pop-rock element, and adds punk feels throughout its play. Moreover, and visually, an animation starts with Lil Nas X’s future-self coming to see the present, broken Lil Nas X sleeping in his bed on a high-ground room; he reaches out through the window then flies away.

As there was a teased snippet of this song available on September 14, 2021, “LOST IN THE CITADEL” marks the eighth track to appear on his studio debut album MONTERO.

songs.full_title: DONT WANT IT by Lil Nas X
songs.title: DONT WANT IT

description.plain:
“DONT WANT IT” is the thirteenth song on Atlanta rapper Lil Nas X’s debut studio album. It features producer credits from Nick Mira and Lil Nas X himself, as this is the first song he’s helped co-produce on.

The song interpolates the folk nursery rhyme “Hush, Little Baby” in its chorus. Lil Nas X isn’t the first rapper to do so—the song was also sampled in Eminem’s “Mockingbird.”

Lil Nas X first previewed the song on Twitter on April 3, 2019, and is confirmed on September 13, 2020, through Instagram stories. The song’s title briefly appeared on screen in Lil Nas X’s futuristic Holiday music video (at 0:49) released on November 13, 2020. This song along with the rest of the album was officially released September 17th, 2021.

songs.full_title: AM I DREAMING by Lil Nas X (Ft. Miley Cyrus)
songs.title: AM I DREAMING

description.plain:
“AM I DREAMING” is the fifteenth and final track off of Lil Nas X’s debut album MONTERO.

The song features Miley Cyrus, an artist who much like Lil Nas X has matured in the public eye and been subject to widespread criticism for exploring her sexuality. The two artists gained unbelievable fame at a young age, but these heartbreaking lyrics reflect the harsh reality they’ve faced as young LGBTQ people in the music industry.

A demo of the same song was leaked 2 months prior to its official release, which features a trimmed length of the song and different vocal parts in the last chorus.

songs.full_title: LIFE AFTER SALEM by Lil Nas X
songs.title: LIFE AFTER SALEM

description.plain:
“LIFE AFTER SALEM” is the fourteenth track from Lil Nas X’s debut album, MONTERO.

Followed by a slow sad rock instrumental, Lil Nas X is probably referring to a person he loves, how he doesn’t love them anymore, that they are changing and that he wants to know what they want from him.

In the leaked version of the project, the song was placed third, but Nas “shook up” the songs and changed the track’s final placement.

The song’s title could also be a reference to the famous Salem Witch Trials. Public figures often use the phrase “witch hunt” to describe waves of public anger or outrage against them. Lil Nas X has experienced multiple waves of public criticism and outrage in his time in the public eye, and now in this song, he is trying to reckon with what it means for him to love after surviving a “witch hunt,” and how the witch hunt changes his view of love and his relationships.

songs.title: Kick It

description.plain:
“Kick It” is the 4th track on Lil Nas X’s debut EP, 7. The track is told by the perspective of a fake friend. In fact, the person speaking in the song has heard about Lil Nas X’s new found success and is trying to act like they were there with Nas from the start: as he doesn’t care about them, they become an hater by throwing dirt on his name, his talent and his credibility as an artist.

It was originally previewed on May 2nd on his Instagram with the caption, “WHAT’S Y'ALL TOP 3 SNIPPETS NOW?!”.
